definition[0]: to grow too big for something
example[0]: They outgrow their clothes so quickly.
example[1]: Harry outgrew his cot when he was about two.
definition[1]: to no longer do or enjoy something that you used to do, because you have grown older and changed
example[2]: Most children eventually outgrow a tendency toward travel sickness.
definition[2]: if a business outgrows a building, it begins to have too many people or too much work to fit into the building
example[3]: His furniture-making business soon outgrew his garage.
definition[3]: to grow or increase faster than someone or something else
